Drowning happens when someone\'s face is under water and they can\'t breathe. It can happen very quickly and quietly.

## Warning Signs
- Someone struggling in water
- Head tilted back, mouth at water level
- Not responding when you call
- Very quiet (drowning is often silent)

## What To Do
- Call for help immediately (911)
- Do NOT jump in unless you are trained
- Throw something that floats
- Use a pole or rope to reach them
- If they are out of the water and not breathing, start CPR

## How to Stay Safe
- Always swim with a buddy
- Never swim alone
- Wear life jackets on boats
- Learn to swim`,
