      explanation: `## Pathophysiology

### Aspiration Effects
- Water aspiration (usually <4 mL/kg)
- Surfactant washout and inactivation
- Alveolar collapse
- V/Q mismatch
- ARDS-like picture

### Hypoxia Cascade
- Cellular hypoxia
- Acidosis
- Cerebral injury (most critical)
- Multi-organ dysfunction

## Clinical Presentation
- Respiratory distress to arrest
- Altered consciousness
- Hypothermia (common)
- Variable cardiovascular status

## Management

### Rescue
- Horizontal extraction
- C-spine precautions if trauma suspected
- Remove from water rapidly

### Resuscitation
- Open airway
- Give rescue breaths (priority in drowning)
- CPR as indicated
- Consider hypothermia

### Post-Resuscitation
- Supplemental oxygen
- Monitor for pulmonary edema
- Evaluate for aspiration pneumonia
- Assess neurological status`,
