### Molecular Lung Injury
- Surfactant protein dysfunction
- SP-A, SP-B inactivation
- Inflammatory cascade activation
- Complement activation
- Neutrophil recruitment

### Cerebral Injury Mechanisms
- Excitotoxicity (glutamate)
- Calcium dysregulation
- Mitochondrial dysfunction
- Apoptosis pathways
- Selective vulnerability patterns

### Hypothermic Neuroprotection
- Reduced cerebral metabolism
- Decreased excitotoxicity
- Anti-inflammatory effects
- Cooling rate considerations

## Evidence-Based Management

### Resuscitation
- ILCOR guidelines emphasis on ventilation
- Duration of CPR in hypothermia
- ECMO considerations
- Targeted temperature management

### Prognostication
| Factor | Favorable | Unfavorable |
|--------|-----------|-------------|
| Submersion | <5 min | >25 min |
| Water temp | Cold | Warm |
| Bystander CPR | Yes | No |
| Initial rhythm | VF/VT | Asystole |
| Pupil response | Present | Absent (unreliable if cold) |

## Long-Term Outcomes
- Hypoxic brain injury spectrum
- Pulmonary complications
- PTSD considerations
- Prevention focus`,
